      Specified by:
      preProcessEvent in interface basilica2.agents.listeners.BasilicaPreProcessor
      Parameters:
      source - the InputCoordinator - to push new events to. (Modified events don't need to be re-pushed).
      event - an incoming event which matches one of this preprocessor's advertised classes (see getPreprocessorEventClasses) Preprocess an incoming event, by modifying this event or creating a new event in response. All original and new events will be passed by the InputCoordinator to the second-stage Reactors ("BasilicaListener" instances).
